          Miller, Sabrina Rossi, Tomaso Belloni, Walter H.G. Lewin
          Comments: 3 pages. Accepted for publication in MNRAS
          We  report  the  result  of  an  XMM-Newton  observation of the
          black-hole  X-ray  transient  XTE  J1650-500 in quiescence. The
          source  was  not detected and we set upper limits on the 0.5-10
          keV  luminosity  of  0.9e31-1.0e31  erg/s  (for a newly derived
          distance  of  2.6  kpc).  These  limits  are  in  line with the
