          We  review  four  mechanisms  for  forming  brown  dwarfs:  (i)
          turbulent  fragmentation  (producing  very  low-mass prestellar
          cores);   (ii)  gravitational  instabilities  in  discs;  (iii)
          dynamical  ejection  of  stellar  embryos  from their placental
          cores;  and  (iv)  photo-erosion  of  pre-existing cores in HII
