          both  highly  compatible  with  known  characteristics  of  the
          structure  and,  along  with previous detections provide radial
          velocity  values  of  the  Ring  over the 120<l<260 range. This
          should  add  strong  constraints  on  numerical  models  of the
          accretion  of  the  dwarf  galaxy  that  is  believed to be the
